thread.title: China Feb soybean imports drop on-yr to 5.4 mln T -Reuters calculation

author: Reuters Editorial
title: China Feb soybean imports drop on-yr to 5.4 mln T -Reuters calculation
text:
BEIJING, March 8 (Reuters) - China imported 5.42 million tonnes of soybeans in February, down 2.2 percent from the same month a year ago, according to Reuters calculations based on customs data released on Thursday.
The volume was the lowest monthly number since October, 2016.
China is the worldâ€™s top soybean importer, and buys 60 percent of the soybeans traded worldwide, mainly from Brazil and the United States, to crush into soymeal used in animal feed. (Reporting by Dominique Patton Editing by Joseph Radford)
